("Light Show","Delhi","Live events","https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-674x446/06/6e/b4/ee.jpg","https://akshardham.com/announcement-open-all-day-aug-21/,","Don t miss the Akshardham light and water show! It s a stunning mix of lights, music & storytelling – super magical in the evening!"),
("Light and Sound  Show","Delhi","Live events","https://itdc.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/BANNER.png","https://in.bookmyshow.com/activities/jai-hind-red-fort-sound-light-show/ET00350160","Red Fort light & sound show is a must-see! It tells Delhi s history with lights, music & voice overs – super immersive vibe!"),
("Hauz Khas","Delhi","Hangout Spots","https://www.mistay.in/travel-blog/content/images/2022/10/Hauz-Khas-Yo-Metro.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/ncr/hauz-khas-village-delhi-restaurants.","Hauz Khas is a chill mix of history and hangout! Explore old ruins, then relax at cool cafes and boutiques nearby. Perfect for a laid-back day!"),
("Connaught Place","Delhi","Hangout Spots","https://static.toiimg.com/photo/48052467.cms","https://www.zomato.com/ncr/connaught-place-delhi-restaurants.","CP  is the heart of Delhi! Great for shopping, eating, chilling, and just soaking in the city vibe!"),,,
("Oh!Max Dream World Theme Park","Delhi","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://res.cloudinary.com/dwzmsvp7f/image/upload/f_auto,w_1280/c_crop%2Cg_custom%2Fv1749108437%2Fg6ypjkxzthpx3tuemd8t.png","https://www.omaxeconnaughtplace.co.in/","Oh!Max Dream World in Greater Noida is an indoor adventure park packed with fun! Walk through the Titanic, secret chambers of Taj, explore jungles, meet dinosaurs, and even make your own chocolate! It s the perfect mix of thrills, fun zones, and magic moments:all under one roof!"),,,
("Oh!Max Dream World Theme Park","Delhi","Hidden Gems","https://res.cloudinary.com/dwzmsvp7f/image/upload/f_auto,w_1280/c_crop%2Cg_custom%2Fv1749108437%2Fg6ypjkxzthpx3tuemd8t.png","https://www.omaxeconnaughtplace.co.in/","Oh!Max Dream World in Greater Noida is an indoor adventure park packed with fun! Walk through the Titanic, secret chambers of Taj, explore jungles, meet dinosaurs, and even make your own chocolate! It s the perfect mix of thrills, fun zones, and magic moments:all under one roof!"),,,
("Gateway of India","Mumbai","Monuments","https://lp-cms-production.imgix.net/2019-06/bbc886323ff07d295157ea35f423e121-gateway-of-india.jpg","https://mumbaicity.gov.in/tourist-place/gateway-of-india/.","Hey!  The Gateway of India is one of Mumbais most iconic landmarks. Built in 1924, it faces the Arabian Sea and was originally constructed to commemorate the visit of King George V and Queen Mary to India.Its a stunning Indo-Saracenic style monument that has become a favorite hangout spot for both tourists and locals. Youll find street food vendors, photographers, and even ferry rides that take you to places like Elephanta Caves . And at night, the entire area lights up beautifully, giving it a magical vibe!Definitely worth a visit if youre exploring Mumbai!."),,,
("Statue of Chatrapati Shivaji Maharaj","Mumbai","Monuments","https://aissms.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/shivaji-maharaj-blog.jpg","https://www.theheritagelab.in/shivaji-statue/.","Hey there! . The Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Monument is a grand upcoming statue being built off the coast of Mumbai, in the Arabian Sea. 🇮🇳 Its dedicated to the legendary Maratha king, Shivaji Maharaj, known for his bravery, smart warfare tactics, and establishing the Maratha Empire.Once completed, its expected to be the tallest statue in the world, even taller than the Statue of Unity!  The location offers stunning sea views, and the monument will also include a museum, amphitheater, and other cultural features to showcase Shivaji Maharajs life and legacy. "),,,
("Haji Ali Dargah","Mumbai","Monuments","https://idsb.tmgrup.com.tr/ly/uploads/images/2021/10/06/150249.jpg","https://www.hajialidargah.in/.","Hey!  The Haji Ali Dargah is one of Mumbais most famous religious and spiritual landmarks. Its a beautiful white marble mosque and tomb located on a small islet off the Worli coast, connected to the mainland by a narrow causeway that gets surrounded by the sea during high tide. The dargah was built in the 15th century and houses the tomb of Pir Haji Ali Shah Bukhari, a wealthy merchant who gave up everything to make a pilgrimage to Mecca. Its visited by people of all faiths who come to seek blessings, enjoy the peaceful vibes, and take in the amazing sea views.The walk to the dargah, especially during sunset, is a unique and serene experience!."),,,
("Kanheri Caves","Mumbai","Monuments","https://historified.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/hq720.jpg","https://sgnp.maharashtra.gov.in/1231/Kanheri-Caves.","Hey there! If youre into history, nature, or a mix of both, Kanheri Caves is a solid spot to check out. Tucked away inside Sanjay Gandhi National Park, its known for its ancient rock-cut Buddhist caves—some dating back over 2,000 years. Youll see beautiful carvings, massive prayer halls, and even old water cisterns. Its a bit of a climb but totally worth it for the peaceful vibe and scenic views. Great for a quiet break from the city rush."),,,
("Shree Siddhivinayak","Mumbai","Temples","https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b9/Shree_Siddhivinayak_Temple_Mumbai.jpg","https://www.siddhivinayak.org/.","Hey! Siddhivinayak Temple is one of the most famous temples in Mumbai, especially for Lord Ganesha devotees. Its located in Prabhadevi and attracts a huge number of visitors every day, including celebrities and politicians. The idol of Ganesha here is carved from a single black stone and looks truly divine. Tuesdays are especially crowded, so if youre planning a peaceful visit, try going on a weekday morning. The vibe is really spiritual, and the temple is very well maintained."),,,
("Shri Mahalakshmi Devi Temple","Mumbai","Temples","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0e/e9/4e/d9/entrance-to-mahalaxmi.jpg?w=1200&h=1200&s=1","https://mumbaicity.gov.in/tourist-place/mahalakshmi-temple/.","Hey! Mahalakshmi Temple is a beautiful and well known temple in Mumbai, dedicated to Goddess Lakshmi along with Saraswati and Kali. Its located near the sea, so the view from the temple is really calming, especially during high tide. The temple gets especially crowded during Navratri when devotees come from all over. The atmosphere is peaceful, and the main shrine has a strong spiritual feel to it. Youll also find small stalls outside selling flowers and prasad its a nice blend of devotion and local charm."),,,
("Shri Mumbadevi Temple","Mumbai","Temples","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0e/d2/87/e3/temple-tower.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1","https://mumbadevi.org.in/.","Hey! Shree Mumbadevi Temple is one of Mumbais oldest and most culturally significant temples. Its dedicated to Goddess Mumbadevi, who is believed to be the citys patron deity yep, Mumbai actually gets its name from her. The temple is located in the busy Zaveri Bazaar area, so the surroundings are always full of life and activity. Inside, the vibe is peaceful and spiritual, with a simple yet sacred idol of the goddess. Its a nice stop if youre exploring the traditional side of the city."),,,
("Iskcon Temple","Mumbai","Temples","https://content3.jdmagicbox.com/v2/comp/mumbai/05/022p7702605/catalogue/hare-rama-hare-krishna-temple-juhu-mumbai-temples-dkibo8zhab.jpg","https://www.iskconmumbai.com.","Hey! ISKCON Temple in Juhu is a really peaceful and beautifully maintained place dedicated to Lord Krishna. Its a spacious temple with white marble architecture, and the interiors are super calming with devotional music playing in the background. Theres a spiritual bookstore, a pure veg Govindas restaurant, and regular aartis that give a very serene vibe. Its just a short walk from Juhu Beach too, so you can plan both together. A perfect spot if youre looking for some quiet time or spiritual energy in the middle of the city."),,,
("Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Terminal","Mumbai","Historical Sites","https://s7ap1.scene7.com/is/image/incredibleindia/chhatrapati-shivaji-maharaj-terminus-mumbai-maharashtra-1-attr-hero?qlt=82&ts=1727355305654","https://www.britannica.com/place/Chhatrapati-Shivaji-Terminus.","Hey! CST, officially known as Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Terminus, is one of Mumbais most iconic landmarks. Its not just a busy railway station, its actually a UNESCO World Heritage Site known for its stunning Victorian Gothic architecture. The building looks especially beautiful at night when its all lit up. Its always buzzing with people since its a major transit point, but if you take a moment to look around, the detailed carvings, domes, and turrets are pretty impressive. A must see if youre into history, architecture, or just soaking in the real Mumbai vibe."),,,
("Flora Fountain","Mumbai","Historical Sites","https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/dd/Mumbai_03-2016_72_Flora_Fountain.jpg","https://exhibits.jioinstitute.edu.in/spotlight/flora-fountain.","Hey! Flora Fountain is a charming little landmark right in the heart of South Mumbai, at the Fort business district. Built in the 1800s during the British era, its got beautiful stone carvings and a classic fountain design that gives you old-world vibes. Its named after the Roman goddess Flora, and though its surrounded by busy streets, it still feels like a slice of history tucked into the city. Great spot for a quick photo or to admire while walking through the heritage filled area nearby."),,,
("Worli Fort","Mumbai","Historical Sites","https://www.gosahin.com/go/p/j/t/1577913116_worli-fort1.jpg","https://historicfortsofindia.blogspot.com/2017/07/worli-fort.html.","Hey! Worli Fort is one of those lesser-known but super interesting historical spots in Mumbai. It was built by the British in the 1600s and sits right by the sea, offering a pretty cool view of the Worli Sea Link and the coastline. The fort itself is small but has that old stone charm, and the surrounding fishing village adds a unique local touch. Its a quiet place not crowded at all so if youre looking for a peaceful spot with some history and sea breeze, its worth a visit."),,,
("Colaba Market","Mumbai","Food Streets","https://b2128690.smushcdn.com/2128690/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DSC_9140.jpg?lossy=2&strip=1&webp=1","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/colaba-restaurants.","Hey! Colaba Market isnt just great for shopping its also a fun place to explore if youre into street food and quick bites. From spicy chaats and vada pavs to kebabs and rolls, theres always something sizzling nearby. Youll find some amazing local stalls around the corners, and Leopold Café or Bagdadi are iconic if you want to sit down for a hearty meal. Whether youre craving Indian snacks or a late night bite after shopping, Colaba Market has that classic Mumbai street food charm."),,,
("Juhu Food Street","Mumbai","Food Streets","https://i.pinimg.com/736x/36/c6/c8/36c6c8ba1223c6d271da58e8807b51dc.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/juhu-restaurants/street-food.","Hey! Juhu is one of the top spots in Mumbai for street food, especially near the beach. The vibe is lively and full of amazing aromas—perfect if youre in the mood for classic Mumbai snacks. Youll find everything from buttery pav bhaji and crispy dosas to sev puri, bhel puri, and spicy vada pav. There are also some sweet treats like kulfi and gola that hit differently by the sea. The stalls are mostly budget friendly and super popular, especially in the evenings. Great place to enjoy food with a view."),,,
("Girgaon Chowpatty","Mumbai","Food Streets","https://pbs.twimg.com/media/ENV-k-rVAAEOKm9.jpg","https://www.holidify.com/places/mumbai/girgaum-chowpatty-sightseeing-2863.html.","Hey! Girgaon Chowpatty is a total street food paradise, especially in the evenings. Youll find all the Mumbai classics—pav bhaji loaded with butter, tangy bhel puri, crispy sev puri, and super refreshing gola (ice lollies in fun flavors like kala khatta and rose),,,. The vibe is super lively with people enjoying the beach, grabbing snacks, and watching the sunset. Its a great mix of tasty, budget-friendly food and chill beachside atmosphere. Perfect place for a fun food walk!."),,,
("Haji Ali Juice Centre","Mumbai","Food Streets","https://imgmediagumlet.lbb.in/media/2025/02/67a05068785fed6c71211054_1738559592250.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/haji-ali-juice-center-tardeo.","Hey! Haji Ali Juice Centre is one of the most iconic juice and snack spots in Mumbai. Its right near the Haji Ali Dargah, and super popular for its fresh fruit juices, creamy milkshakes, and loaded faloodas. Theyve also got sandwiches, pizzas, and fruit with cream mango cream is a crowd favorite when in season. The place is always buzzing, especially in the evenings, and the quality has stayed top notch for years. Great spot to chill and grab something refreshing after exploring the area."),,,
("Joggers Park","Mumbai","Parks and Gardens","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/16/84/ea/c3/inside-jogger-s-park.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1","https://www.tripadvisor.in/Attraction_Review-g304554-d321403-Reviews-Jogger_s_Park-Mumbai_Maharashtra.html.","Hey! Joggers Park in Bandra is a peaceful green escape right by the sea perfect if youre into walking, jogging, or just relaxing outdoors. Its super popular with locals for morning and evening walks, and the sea breeze makes it even better. Theres a well-maintained track, open spaces, and benches where you can just sit and chill. Youll often spot kids playing, people doing yoga, or couples enjoying the sunset. Its clean, calm, and a great break from the citys chaos."),,,
("Azad Maidan","Mumbai","Parks and Gardens","https://content.jdmagicbox.com/v2/comp/mumbai/m4/022pxx22.xx22.220521092847.t1m4/catalogue/azad-maidan-court-fort-mumbai-sports-ground-xZq1IgOSbr.jpg","https://indianculture.gov.in/node/2816117.","Hey! Azad Maidan is a big open ground in South Mumbai, right near CST. Its super famous for cricket. Youll always find young players practicing there, and some legends like Sachin and Prithvi Shaw started out here. The place also has a lot of history; its been used for political rallies and protests since the freedom movement days. Its got that old school Mumbai vibe dusty pitches, city buzz, and tons of energy all around."),,,
("Amarsons Park","Mumbai","Parks and Gardens","https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/12/b4/d4/9f/photo1jpg.jpg","https://www.justdial.com/Mumbai/Amarson-Garden-Breach-Candy/022PXX22-XX22-121116142512-L5Q9_BZDET.","Hey! Amarsons Garden, also known as Harish Mahindra Childrens Park, is a peaceful spot in Breach Candy right by the sea. Its great for families. Theres a play area with swings, slides, and even a giant chess board. The walking paths and shady benches make it perfect for a chill stroll or just relaxing with a sea breeze. Its clean, well kept, and ideal for a quiet morning or sunset hangout. There are even a few snack stalls outside for a quick bite."),,,
("Colaba Market","Mumbai","https://topicimages.mrowl.com/large/rohitkap/topoutdoormark/colabacauseway_1.jpg","Markets","https://www.makemytrip.com/tripideas/attractions/shopping-at-colaba-causeway-market.","Hey! Colaba Market is one of Mumbais most popular street shopping spots, especially for tourists. Its packed with stalls and tiny shops selling everything from clothes, jewelry, bags, and antiques to souvenirs and quirky décor items. Bargaining is totally expected here, so dont hesitate to haggle a bit! The market is just a short walk from Gateway of India, and while youre there, you can also grab some street food or chill at iconic places like Café Leopold or Mondegar. The vibe is lively, colorful, and full on Mumbai energy."),,,
("Fashion Street","Mumbai","Markets","https://cdn2.stylecraze.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/1.-Colaba-Causeway-Market.jpg.webp","https://www.justdial.com/Mumbai/Fashion-Street-Opposite-Bombay-Zymkhana-Churchgate/022PXX22-XX22-191227211833-U5E5_BZDET.","Hey! Fashion Street is a go to spot in South Mumbai if youre into trendy clothes at budget prices. Its a long stretch lined with street side stalls selling everything from jeans, tops, and dresses to shoes, caps, and accessories. Perfect for college students and anyone who loves to mix and match styles. Youll need to bargain; thats part of the fun here! Its right near CST and Churchgate, so super easy to reach. The vibe is fast paced, colorful, and full of street fashion energy."),,,
("National Gallery of Modern Art","Mumbai","Art and Culture","https://s7ap1.scene7.com/is/image/incredibleindia/national-gallery-of-modern-art-mumbai-maharashtra-4-musthead-hero?qlt=82&ts=1727355342860","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/maharashtra/mumbai/national-gallery-of-modern-art.","Hey! The National Gallery of Modern Art in Mumbai is a great spot if youre into art and culture. Its located in Colaba, right near the Kala Ghoda area, and housed in a beautiful heritage building. The gallery features modern and contemporary Indian art, with works by legends like Amrita Sher-Gil, F.N. Souza, and M.F. Husain.The space is calm, nicely lit, and perfect for browsing at your own pace. They also host rotating exhibitions, workshops, and cultural events from time to time. If youre in the area and want something peaceful and creative to explore, NGMA is a solid choice."),,,
("Jehangir Art Gallery","Mumbai","Art and Culture","https://media1.thrillophilia.com/filestore/6xlahww9uqlpjir2zq97x0zrskkh_1573451466_jehangir.jpg?w=400&dpr=2","https://jehangirartgallery.com/.","Hey! Jehangir Art Gallery is one of Mumbais most iconic and oldest art spaces, located in the Kala Ghoda area. Its been around since 1952 and is known for showcasing a wide range of contemporary and traditional Indian art. From paintings and sculptures to photography and mixed media, the exhibits change regularly, so theres always something new to see.The gallery is free to enter and has a simple, peaceful vibe perfect if youre in the mood to explore some creative work. Its also right next to popular spots like the Prince of Wales Museum and several cafés, so you can easily make a day of it. Great place if youre curious about Indias modern art scene!."),,,
("Elephanta Caves","Mumbai","Art and Culture","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT6WDJkAeIQmvxqLEM0eSr-NEX8z3JmdEIHsg&s","https://elephanta.co.in/.","Hey! Elephanta Caves is a great day trip from Mumbai if youre into history and rock-cut architecture. Its located on Elephanta Island, about an hours ferry ride from the Gateway of India. Once you reach the island, theres a short uphill walk (or toy train + steps),,, to the caves.The main attraction is Cave 1, dedicated to Lord Shiva, with stunning sculptures like the huge Trimurti, a three faced image representing Shiva as creator, protector, and destroyer. The caves date back to the 5th to 7th centuries and are a UNESCO World Heritage Site.Youll also find a few smaller caves, some Buddhist ones, and great sea views from the top. Its open every day except Monday, and its best to visit in cooler months like October to March. Just remember to carry water and watch out for monkeys they love snacks!."),,,
("The Bombay Art Society","Mumbai","Art and Culture","https://www.bandrabuzz.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/The-Bombay-Art-Society-Bandra.jpg","https://bombayartsociety.org/.","The Bombay Art Society is one of the oldest art institutions in India, located in Bandra, Mumbai. Its a great place to explore contemporary Indian art, with regular exhibitions showcasing works by both emerging and established artists. The building itself has a very unique, modern design that stands out. If youre into art or just want to browse something different, its definitely worth a visit."),,,
("Leopold Cafe","Mumbai","Cafes","https://im.whatshot.in/img/2019/Feb/collage-colaba-2-cropped-1551091415.jpg?wm=1&w=1200&h=630&cc=1","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/leopold-cafe-bar-colaba.","hey! Their Leopold Café in Colaba is one of Mumbais most iconic spots. Its been around since 1871 and still pulls in a crowd every day. The vibe is casual and old school, with a mix of locals, backpackers, and tourists. The menu has a bit of everything Indian, Chinese, Continental and the portions are big. Its also known for its connection to the 2008 attacks, with some of the bullet marks still visible. If youre in the area, its a cool place to grab a bite, chill, and take in a bit of Mumbais history."),,,
("Prithv("Lotus Temple ","Delhi","Temples","https://sceneloc8.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/1-41.png","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/delhi/delhi/lotus-temple","The Lotus Temple blossoms with peace and unity : a silent sanctuary where every heart is welcome. "),
("Red Fort","Delhi","Monuments","https://img.indiahighlight.com/1170x550/ih/uploads/1696599198.jpg","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/delhi/delhi/red-fort","The Red Fort stands proud and majestic : a symbol of Indias rich heritage and the voice of freedom echoing through time. "),
("Akshardham Mandir","Delhi", "Temples","https://www.goldentriangletour.com/userfiles/1_Swaminarayan%20Akshardham%20Complex,%20New%20Delhi.jpg","https://delhitourism.gov.in/tourist_place/akshardham_temple.html","Akshardham Mandir is a divine masterpiece : where art, spirituality, and serenity come together in breathtaking harmony. "),
("Jhandewala Hanuman Temple","Delhi","Temples","https://www.exploreourindia.com/backend/web/images/post/big/6712_Jhandewalan-Hanuman-Mandir.webp","https://www.justdial.com/Delhi/Hanuman-Mandir-Near-Jhandewalan-Extension-Near-Jhandewalan-Metro-Station-Jhandewalan/011PXX11-XX11-140510152649-Y5X4_BZDET","Jhandewalan Hanuman Mandir radiates strength and devotion : a towering symbol of faith that fills every heart with courage and peace. "),
("Iskon Temple","Delhi","Temples","https://www.templepurohit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/2-2.jpg","https://www.iskcondelhi.com/","ISKCON Temple is a haven of devotion and joy : where chants, love, and divine energy fill the air with bliss.  Hare Krishna!"),i Cafe","Mumbai","Cafes","https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/prithvi_cafe_1601650143936.jpg?bg=2d2822&crop=1000%2C667%2Cnull%2C0&fit=fill&fitToScale=h%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=768&height=667&w=1368&width=1000","http://zomato.com/mumbai/prithvi-cafe-juhu.","Prithvi Cafe in Mumbai is a chilled out spot right next to the iconic Prithvi Theatre in Juhu. Its got a relaxed open-air vibe with lots of greenery, making it a favourite for artists, students, and locals alike. The menu has a nice mix of Indian and continental options, try their Irish coffee and parathas, theyre quite popular. Its a great place to hang out, read, or just enjoy a slow meal."),,,
("Pizza By The Bay","Mumbai","Cafes","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/05/02/15/38/pizza-by-the-bay.jpg?w=900&h=-1&s=1","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/pizza-by-the-bay-churchgate/menu .","Hey foodie!Pizza by the Bay is a well known café on Marine Drive with a great sea view and a relaxed, classy vibe. Its popular for its pizzas, pastas, and all day breakfast menu. The place has both indoor and outdoor seating, and its a nice spot to enjoy a meal while watching the waves. It can be a bit pricey, and reviews on the food are mixed, but the location and atmosphere make it worth visiting at least once especially around sunset."),,,
("Bay view Cafe","Mumbai","Cafes","https://imgmediagumlet.lbb.in/media/2020/11/5fa3d6a63404046c9b7a560f_1604572838823.png","https://www.zomato.com/mumbai/bayview-cafe-colaba.","Hey their !Bay View Cafe in Colaba is a simple rooftop spot with a laid back atmosphere and a great view of the sea. Its not fancy, but its loved for its location and chill vibe. The menu has a mix of Indian and continental food, think sandwiches, pizzas, biryanis, and mocktails. Its a good place to unwind in the evening, especially if youre looking for something casual and budget friendly near the Gateway of India."),,,
("EsselWorld","Mumbai","Amusement/Theme Parks ","https://media.tacdn.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-674x446/06/71/ae/1b.jpg","https://www.makemytrip.com/tripideas/attractions/essel-world.","Essel World Water Kingdom is a fun spot if youre looking to beat the heat. Its one of the largest water parks in India with a bunch of cool rides, wave pools, lazy river, and slides for all age groups. The place can get crowded on weekends, so its better to go early. Good for a day trip with friends or family."),,,
("Water kingdom","Mumbai","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://assets.simplotel.com/simplotel/image/upload/x_0,y_215,w_1610,h_905,r_0,c_crop/q_80,w_900,dpr_1,f_auto,fl_progressive,c_limit/essel-world/WETLANTI_ggr8l2","https://www.waterkingdom.in/ .","Its a solid spot to cool off and have fun with friends or family. If youre up for big slides and wave pools, this is a cool escape from city heat. Weekdays are the sweet spot less crowd and smoother experience."),,,
("Tikuji ni Wadi","Mumbai","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://tripxl.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Location-93.jpg","https://www.tikuji-ni-wadi.com/ .","If you want a fun mix water slides, chill river rides, amusement park karts, plus a stroll among dinosaurs this place hits the spot. Easy to do in a day, good for a family outing or friend group. Weekdays or non holiday weekends is equal to  better vibe, fewer crowds."),,,
("Kidzania","Mumbai","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://images.livemint.com/rf/Image-621x414/LiveMint/Period1/2013/08/17/Photos/90811176[1]--621x414.jpg","https://india.kidzania.com/en-in/pages/mumbai-pricing. ","kidzania is a fun, safe spot where kids get to play grownups—earn money, spend it, learn new jobs—all while parents relax. Great for a few hours or a full day, especially on a weekday."),,,
("Maratha Mandir","Mumbai","Movie Theatres","https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/01/20/multimedia/20india-cinema-2-812b/00india-cinema-2-812b-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&auto=webp&disable=upscale","https://in.bookmyshow.com/cinemas/mumbai/maratha-mandir-mumbai-central/MMMC/20250618 .","Looking for a slice of Mumbais film buff culture? Watching DDLJ here feels like stepping back in time. Its simple, sentimental, a little loud and totally worth the experience. "),,,
("Nexus Seawoods","Mumbai","Movie Theatres","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ2nOtJZll8RrjlUujowtJ83KX8eHfFG4bnNg&s","https://www.nexusselecttrust.com/nexus-seawood .","If youre up for a big screen experience or want to try IMAX/4DX, this place has the tech and comfort. But heads up the premium formats can be pricey, and the IMAX visuals sometimes disappoint. For that laid back movie night, stick to Dolby 7.1 or VIP seats youll get comfy seating without breaking the bank."),,,
("Viviana Mall","Mumbai","Movie Theatres","https://vivianamalls.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Home-Page-Banner-Desktop.png","https://vivianamalls.com/ .","Viviana Mall in Thane is a great spot if youre looking for a mix of shopping, food, and fun. Its got a bunch of popular brands, a big Cinepolis theatre with IMAX and 4DX, and a fun zone with games and bowling. The food court has plenty of options too good for families or just hanging out with friends. Super accessible and pretty lively, especially on weekends."),,,
("Film city tour","Mumbai","Hidden Gems","https://content.jdmagicbox.com/v2/comp/mumbai/e2/022pxx22.xx22.200628121940.y8e2/catalogue/film-city-mandir-goregaon-east-mumbai-temples-r72tx6r4uu.jpg","https://www.filmcitymumbai.org/ ","If youre curious about how Bollywood works a peek behind the scenes, exploring live sets, catching a glimpse of shooting in progress this is worth doing once. Tours arent blockbuster experiences, but theyre a decent insider pass into film making. Just book in advance, go early, and enjoy soaking in the film city energy."),,,
("Oberoi Mall","Mumbai","Shopping Malls","https://d3oazelycifulb.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/diwali-blog.jpg","https://www.oberoimall.com/ .","Oberoi Mall in Goregaon East is a nice and compact place if youre up for some shopping, food, or catching a movie. It has good brand options, a clean vibe, and a PVR with comfy seats. Theres also an arcade and a food court with plenty of choices. Easy to reach from the highway or metro, and not too chaotic like some other malls. Great for a relaxed outing."),,,
("R city Mall","Mumbai","Shopping Malls","https://static.squareyards.com/resources/images/mumbai/project-image/r-city-mall-project-project-large-image1-6139.jpg","https://rcity.in/ ","R City Mall in Ghatkopar is a big, all in one kind of place. Youve got loads of shopping brands, plenty of food options, a multiplex, and fun stuff like Kidzania, Snow Kingdom, and Timezone. Its a good pick whether youre going with family, friends, or just for a casual outing. Easily reachable by metro and road, and theres always something going on inside."),,,
("Phoenix Marketcity","Mumbai","Shopping Malls","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSjzs8ZfXQGtUJ_f0gx8VtlQqruN1tHSt3PLA&s","https://www.phoenixmarketcity.com/mumbai","Phoenix Marketcity is a one stop destination for shopaholics, foodies, cinephiles, and anyone up for gaming or unique experiences like ice skating or simulating a flight. A full day hangout thats lively yet comfy just get there early, especially on weekends."),,,
("Infinity Mall","Mumbai","Shopping Malls","https://d3mbwbgtcl4x70.cloudfront.net/Screenshot_2024_11_11_215328_e5b43167d8.webp,https://www.infinitimall.com/","Infinity Mall Malad is basically an all rounder with great shops, solid food choices, fun games, and a good movie theater. Its lively but not overwhelming, perfect for a relaxed full day hangout with friends or family.");

INSERT INTO place (name, city, category,image_url,booking_link, description)
VALUES 
("Taj Mahal","Agra","Monuments","https://static.wixstatic.com/media/055605_65e20a7fcbc54e2e8720adfc2544c35e~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_1800,h_1082,al_c,q_85/taj_new_contant_edited.jpg","https://tajmahal.gov.in/","Taj Mahal is a breathtaking symbol of love and one of the most iconic wonders in the world.Its gleaming white marble, intricate carvings, and serene gardens create a dreamy, almost magical vibe. Whether youre a history buff, a romantic, or just love beautiful places, the Taj is an experience youll never forget. Sunrise or sunset—its pure magic every time!"),
("Agra Fort", "Agra", "Monuments","https://www.exoticmiles.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Agra-Fort.jpg", "https://www.tajmahal.gov.in/agrafort.aspx","Agra Fort is a grand red sandstone fortress that once housed emperors and echoed with royal tales. Walk through majestic halls, hidden passages, and balconies with views of the Taj! Every corner whispers Mughal history and power. A perfect blend of strength, beauty, and legacy!"),
("Mankameshwar Temple", "Agra", "Temples","https://www.indiaeasytrip.com/states-of-india/mankameshwar-temple.jpg", "https://agratourism.in/shri-mankameshwar-mandir-agra","Mankameshwar Temple in Agra is a sacred and serene spot dedicated to Lord Shiva.Tucked in the heart of the old city, its believed that wishes made here come true. With its peaceful vibe, ancient charm, and devotional energy, its a spiritual escape from the citys bustle. "),
("Shri Ram Bagh Temple", "Agra", "Temples","https://kevinstandagephotography.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ksp_6313.jpg?w=1024", "https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/uttar-pradesh/agra/ram-bagh","Shri Ram Bagh, also known as Aram Bagh, is one of Agras oldest and most historic Mughal gardens.Built by Emperor Babur in 1528, its name means Garden of Rest, and it truly lives up to it! Set along the banks of the Yamuna River, just 5 km from the Taj Mahal, it offers peaceful greenery, flowing water channels, and a quiet royal charm—perfect for a calm stroll through history. "),
("Fatehpur Sikri", "Agra", "Monuments","https://cdn.thedecorjournalindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Fatehpur-Sikri-An-Architectural-Marvel-carved-with-Intricacy-and-Royalty-1.jpg", "https://tajmahal.gov.in/fatehpur-sikri.aspx","Fatehpur Sikri is a stunning red sandstone city built by Emperor Akbar in the 16th century.Once the Mughal capital, its filled with grand palaces, courtyards, and the famous Buland Darwaza—one of the tallest gateways in the world! Every step here feels like a walk through a royal tale, frozen in time. "),
("Akbar Tomb", "Agra", "Monuments","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ3IbbXhdbH0x7_5_NE2_j_inGz_8iDnUZc0g&s", "https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/uttar-pradesh/agra/akbar-s-tomb-sikandara","Akbars Tomb in Sikandra is a majestic blend of Mughal art and architecture, built for one of Indias greatest emperors.Surrounded by lush gardens and grand gateways, the tomb is peaceful, powerful, and beautifully detailed. A timeless tribute to the visionary Akbar—where history rests in royal silence."),
("Mehtab Bagh", "Agra", "Historical Sites","https://www.hoteldekho.com/storage/img/tourattraction/1644831440mehtab-bagh-front-view-featured.jpg", "https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/uttar-pradesh/agra/mehtab-bagh","Mehtab Bagh is a beautiful riverside garden that offers one of the best views of the Taj Mahal.Located right across the Yamuna, its perfect for a peaceful stroll, especially at sunset when the Taj glows in the golden light. A hidden gem for nature lovers, photographers, and romantics alike!"),
("Akbar Tomb", "Agra", "	Historical Sites ","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ3IbbXhdbH0x7_5_NE2_j_inGz_8iDnUZc0g&s", "https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/uttar-pradesh/agra/akbar-s-tomb-sikandara","Akbars Tomb in Sikandra is a majestic blend of Mughal art and architecture, built for one of Indias greatest emperors.Surrounded by lush gardens and grand gateways, the tomb is peaceful, powerful, and beautifully detailed. A timeless tribute to the visionary Akbar—where history rests in royal silence."),
("Sadar Bazaar", "Agra", "Food Streets","https://www.grandindiatours.com/images/agra-food-tour-with-sadar-bazar-walk.jpg", "https://traveltriangle.com/blog/sadar-bazaar/","Sadar Bazaar in Agra is the go-to spot for food lovers!From tangy chaats and sizzling snacks to sweet kulfis and shakes, its packed with mouthwatering street food. The market buzzes with energy, flavors, and fun—perfect for an evening stroll after sightseeing. A true local food adventure!"),
("Kinari Bazaar", "Agra", "Food Streets","https://content.jdmagicbox.com/comp/agra/61/0562p562std3161/catalogue/chokho-jeeman-marwari-jain-bhojnalya-delhi-gate-agra-restaurants-w390imjlvm.jpg", "https://backpackersunited.in/destinations/agra/attraction/kinari-bazaar","Kinari Bazaar in Agra isnt just a shoppers paradise—its a street food heaven too! From spicy kachoris and crispy samosas to rich sweets like petha and jalebi, every corner serves up authentic local flavors. The narrow lanes are filled with delicious aromas and buzzing energy—perfect for a tasty break while exploring!"),
("Friends Gokulam Fun City", "Agra", "Amusement/Theme Parks","https://res.cloudinary.com/kmadmin/image/upload/v1624440403/kiomoi/Agra_Friends_Gokulam_Fun_City_Water_Park_1624440402203.jpg", "https://www.tripinvites.com/places/agra/friends-gokulam-fun-city-water-park/","Friends Gokulam Fun City is Agras ultimate spot for water slides, wave pools, and non stop fun! Perfect for families and friends, its the coolest way to beat the heat and splash into joy. Get ready for thrills, chills, and lots of laughter!"),
("Sadar Bazaar", "Agra", "Markets","https://imgcld.yatra.com/ytimages/image/upload/t_yt_blog_w_800_c_fill_g_auto_q_auto:good_f_jpg/v1467107657/Agra_Shopping_Shahin_Arts.jpg", "https://traveltriangle.com/blog/sadar-bazaar/","Sadar Bazaar in Agra is a lively market buzzing with colors, crowds, and great finds! From trendy clothes and leather goods to souvenirs and sweets, its a shoppers paradise. Perfect for picking up gifts or just enjoying the local vibe after a day of sightseeing! "),
("Kinari Bazaar", "Agra", "Markets","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRFFeYH-8GZrq7xRCnK92mMCRgSFKta1nVztA&s", "https://backpackersunited.in/destinations/agra/attraction/kinari-bazaar","Kinari Bazaar in Agra is a vibrant maze of narrow lanes filled with sparkle and tradition!Known for its bridal wear, jewelry, handicrafts, and festive decorations, its a treasure trove for shoppers. If you love colorful chaos and hidden gems, this market is a must-visit! "),
("Marble Inlay Workshops(near Taj),,", "Agra", "Art and Culture","https://kalakritiagra.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Steps_Step-9-721x1024.jpg", "https://powertraveller.com/marble-inlay-workshop-tour-in-agra/?srsltid=AfmBOoqS9nFhqF_a2LXY0vs4B0NUmZqCxhTfrpo2CdZaJlIlNGtVoeeH","Explore Agras marble inlay workshops just steps from the Taj!Watch master craftsmen embed gleaming semi-precious stones into white marble—a tradition dating back to the artisans of the Taj Mahal.Get hands-on, chat with descendants of the original artisans, and maybe take home a handcrafted keepsake—each piece is a tiny masterpiece you helped create!"),
("The Salt cafe", "Agra", "Cafes","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/26/c0/d8/e0/beautiful-3rd-level-rooftop.jpg?w=1400&h=-1&s=1", "https://www.tripadvisor.in/Restaurant_Review-g297683-d15207883-Reviews-The_Salt_Cafe_Kitchen_Bar-Agra_Agra_District_Uttar_Pradesh.html","The Salt Café in Agra is a chill, stylish spot perfect for casual hangouts and cozy dinners.With rooftop seating, fairy lights, and live music vibes, its a total mood! From Indian curries to sushi and pasta, the menu has it all. Great food, warm ambience, and Insta-worthy corners!"),
("Chia Taj View Cafe", "Agra", "Cafes","https://content.jdmagicbox.com/v2/comp/agra/w1/0562px562.x562.221229182534.z8w1/catalogue/chia-taj-view-cafe-tajganj-agra-fast-food-qrjq12lle0-250.jpg", "https://www.tripadvisor.in/Restaurant_Review-g297683-d25019534-Reviews-Chia_Taj_View_Cafe-Agra_Agra_District_Uttar_Pradesh.html","Chia Taj View Cafe in Agra is your rooftop haven with jaw-dropping Taj Mahal views! Sip on masala chai or espresso, feast on aloo parathas or pasta, and chill in cozy, colorful vibes. The staff, led by friendly folks like Sanjeev and Rahul, make you feel right at home. Open from early morning till late evening—perfect for sunrise magic or sunset moments over the Taj!"),
("Sheroes Hangout Cafe", "Agra", "Cafes","https://imgcld.yatra.com/ytimages/image/upload/t_yt_blog_c_fill_q_auto:good_f_auto_w_800_h_500/v1477907112/Sheroes_Cafe_Agra_Exterior_1477907109.jpg", "https://planeterra.org/sheroes-hangout/","Sheroes Hangout Café in Agra is more than just a café—its a powerful space of courage and hope. Run by acid attack survivors, it offers delicious food in a colorful, inspiring setting. Guests are welcomed with warmth, and the pay as you wish vibe makes it even more special. A must-visit with a heart!"),
("Shree Cinema", "Agra", "Movie Theatres","https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/16/6d/15/54/silver-class.jpg", "https://shreecinema.com/","Shree Cinema in Agra is a classic single-screen gem with modern flair! Featuring crisp 2K digital (4K-adapted),, projection and Dolby Atmos sound, it delivers a top-tier viewing experience. Cozy interiors, comfy seating, and a budget-friendly café make it feel like a mini-multiplex—perfect for a fun outing with friends or family. Some visitors rave about the audio and ambience, though a few note its best enjoyed with pals!"),
("Meher Cinema", "Agra", "Movie Theatres","https://cdn3.ticketnew.com/partners/img/Meher_Cinema/images/4.jpg", "https://www.mehercinema.com/","Meher Cinema in Agra blends old-school charm with modern tech, offering a big screen, digital sound, and comfy seating.Its a favorite for locals looking for a quality movie experience at pocket-friendly prices. From tasty snacks to spacious halls, its perfect for a chill film outing with friends or family!"),
("Ashok Cosmos Mall", "Agra", "Shopping Malls","https://ashokcosmosmall.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/GalImg4.jpg", "https://ashokcosmosmall.com/","Ashok Cosmos Mall in Agra is a vibrant one-stop destination for shopping, dining, and entertainment! With top brands, a modern cinema, fun zones, and tasty food spots like Barbeque Nation and McDonalds, its perfect for a family day out or a chill hangout. Spacious, clean, and packed with energy!"),
("Sarv SRK Mall", "Agra", "Shopping Malls","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcR7AALhwEeKA4BfowFPJt0Evr70uyWemTVM-w&s", "https://yappe.in/uttar-pradesh/agra/sarv-srk-mall/280996","Sarv SRK Mall in Agra is a lively spot for shopping, food, and fun!With popular brands, a food court featuring Burger King and Ghoomar Thali, and a 7-screen Sarv Multiplex, its perfect for both casual hangouts and family outings. Dont miss the vibrant kids play zone for little adventurers! ");



INSERT INTO place (name, city, category,image_url,booking_link, description)
VALUES
('Hawa Mahal','Jaipur','Monuments','https://theheritageart.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/hawa-mahal.jpg','https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/rajasthan/jaipur/hawa-mahal ','Hawa Mahal in Jaipur is a beautiful pink sandstone structure known for its unique architecture with hundreds of small windows called jharokhas. It was built in 1799 so royal women could observe street festivals without being seen. The place has a breezy charm, especially in the early morning, and gives a great view of the city from the top floors. Its a quick visit but definitely worth it for photos and the vibe.'),
("Amber Fort","Jaipur","Monuments","https://treeofliferesorts.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/beautifoul-amber-fort-near-jaipur-city-india-rajasthan_431724-2850.jpg","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/rajasthan/jaipur/amber-fort.","Amber Fort is one of the most iconic spots in Jaipur, known for its grand architecture and hilltop setting. Built in the 16th century, it blends Rajput and Mughal styles and has beautiful courtyards, palaces, and temples inside. The Sheesh Mahal (mirror palace), is especially stunning. You can either walk up, take a jeep, or ride an elephant to the fort. Its a great place to explore if you enjoy history, architecture, and scenic views."),
("Jantar Mantar","Jaipur","Monuments","https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/91352918/Jantar-Mantar-Jaipur.jpg?width=636&height=358&resize=4","https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1338/ .","Jantar Mantar in Jaipur is an interesting stop, especially if youre into astronomy or curious old structures. Its an observatory built in the 18th century by Maharaja Jai Singh II and features giant instruments that were used to measure time, predict eclipses, and track stars. The precision of these instruments is pretty impressive even today. Its a peaceful place to walk around and learn something unique about science and history."),
("Nahargarh Fort","Jaipur","Monuments","https://www.remotelands.com/travelogues/app/uploads/2019/01/Amber-fort-header.jpg","https://obms-tourist.rajasthan.gov.in/place-details/Nahagarh-Fort .","Nahargarh Fort sits on the Aravalli hills and gives one of the best views of Jaipur, especially at sunset. It was originally built in the 18th century as a retreat and part of the citys defense system. The fort has a mix of rugged charm and elegant architecture, and the palace area inside is worth exploring. Theres also a small café where you can chill and enjoy the view. Its a nice spot if youre looking to spend a relaxed couple of hours with scenic surroundings."),
("Birla Mandir","Jaipur","Temples","https://rajasthanyatra.in/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/birla.webp","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/rajasthan/jaipur/birla-temple .","Birla Mandir in Jaipur is a peaceful and beautifully maintained temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu and Goddess Lakshmi. Built entirely in white marble, it stands out with its clean look and detailed carvings. The temple isnt very large, but the atmosphere is calm, especially in the evening when its lit up. Its a good spot to visit for some quiet time or if youre into architecture and spirituality.."),
("Thikana Mandir","Jaipur","Temples","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ5fA9FrlysOXLFsktofNv-LU5VTGMQJvLFbQ&s","https://mandirshrigovinddevjijaipur.org/.","Thikana Mandir in Jaipur is a charming under the radar temple that blends local craftsmanship with a cozy, almost boutique-like charm. Unlike the large, marble built famed temples, this one feels more intimate and serene ideal for visitors seeking a quieter spiritual experience. The temple architecture highlights regional Rajasthani style with colorful murals and intricate stonework. People often go there for its peaceful ambiance rather than pilgrim crowds. If youre wandering through Jaipur and want a little break from the tourist spots, its a lovely, gentle stop."),
("Moti Dungri Ganesh ji","Jaipur","Temples","https://www.motidungri.com/images/gallery-2.jpg","https://www.motidungri.com/ .","If youre exploring Jaipurs spiritual and cultural spots, Moti Dungri offers a beautiful mix of devotion, history, and viewrich ambiance—especially if timed right during aarti or festival."),
("Shri Akshardham Temple","Jaipur","Temples","https://www.trawell.in/admin/images/upload/151648138Jaipur_Akshardham_Temple_Main.jpg","https://www.tripadvisor.in/Attraction_Review-g304555-d3913346-Reviews-Akshardham_Temple-Jaipur_Jaipur_District_Rajasthan.html .","Shree Akshardham Temple in Jaipur (also known as the Swaminarayan Mandir), is a majestic modern temple complex, blending beautiful craftsmanship, spiritual ambiance, and green surroundings—well worth a spot on your Jaipur itinerary."),
("The City Palace","Jaipur","Historical Sites","https://s7ap1.scene7.com/is/image/incredibleindia/city-palace-jaipur-rajasthan-1?qlt=82&ts=1726660027704","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/rajasthan/jaipur/city-palace .","City Palace in Jaipur is a grand royal complex located right in the heart of the city. Its got a beautiful mix of Rajasthani and Mughal architecture, with big courtyards, museums, and detailed gates—especially the Peacock Gate which everyone loves clicking pictures at. Parts of it are still home to the royal family, while others are open to the public with exhibits of royal clothes, weapons, and old artifacts. You can easily spend a few hours here, and its especially nice to visit in the morning or late afternoon when its not too hot."),
("Jal Mahal","Jaipur","Historical Sites","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/c4/72/f6/jal-mahal-jaipur-tour.jpg?w=900&h=500&s=1","https://www.incredibleindia.gov.in/en/rajasthan/jaipur/jal-mahal .","Jal Mahal is a serene and scenic spot in Jaipur, located right in the middle of Man Sagar Lake. The palace looks like its floating on water and gives off a really peaceful vibe, especially around sunset. While visitors cant go inside the palace itself, the view from the lakeside is beautiful and makes for great photos. Youll also find locals selling snacks, souvenirs, and even offering camel rides along the promenade. Its a quick but memorable stop, perfect if youre looking to just relax and enjoy the view."),
("Jawahar Circle Street","Jaipur","Food Streets","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTeym0sGAo_HZFlZLaEsBZqc9IWNBKdXhKX3w&s","https://www.justdial.com/Jaipur/Jawahar-Circle-Street-Food-Bazar/0141PX141-X141-200628000747-C9E4_BZDET .","Hey foodie! if youre up for a short street food adventure, spending 45 to 60 minutes here lets you sample Jaipurs favorite quick bites with the lovely ambiance of the circle and fountain show."),
("Masala Chowk","Jaipur","Food Streets","https://d3gw4aml0lneeh.cloudfront.net/assets/locations/15094/fUE2EatnAClG.jpg","https://obms-tourist.rajasthan.gov.in/place-details/Masala-Chowk .","Masala Chowk (also called Spice Street), in Jaipur is an inviting open-air food court nestled in Ram Niwas Garden, right behind the Albert Hall Museum. For just a small entry fee (around ₹10),, youll find over 20 clean, well-maintained stalls serving a wide range of local and panIndian street eats—from crispy pyaaz kachori, samosas, golgappas, and mirchi badas to South Indian dosas, faloodas, shakes, and desserts like ghewar and rabri."),
("Food Street","Jaipur","Food Streets","https://roamingjack.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-street-food-in-jaipur-roaming-jack.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/restaurants/in/world-trade-park-malviya-nagar .","Food Street at World Trade Park in Jaipur is a lively rooftop style food court thats perfect if youre craving a mix of local and international eats. Youll find everything from pani puri and chaats to pizzas, burgers, noodles, and desserts. The whole space has a fun, open-air vibe with stylish decor, making it a nice place to chill with friends or family after shopping. It can get a bit crowded in the evenings, but the variety of food makes it worth a visit. Great spot for quick bites or even a full meal, especially if youre already around WTP."),
("Kolkata Chat Bandar","Jaipur","Food Streets","https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/reviews_photos/b18/4433537884a2139025b5f3212bb84b18_1584605312.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/kalkatta-chat-bhandar-c-scheme .","Kolkata Chaat Bhandar in C-Scheme, near the High Court, is a super popular street food spot in Jaipur, especially known for its massive and delicious dahi vada and paneer chilla. The portions are big enough for two people, and the flavors are spot on tangy, creamy, and loaded with chutneys. The place is run by Pandit ji, whos been serving locals for decades with a warm vibe. Its a no-frills setup, usually crowded in the evenings, but totally worth the wait if youre craving some classic Jaipur-style chaat."),
("Fun Kingdom","Jaipur","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://www.tripozia.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fun-kingdom-jaipur.jpg","https://funkingdomjaipur.com/ .","Fun Kingdom in Mansarovar, Jaipur is a fun-packed amusement and adventure park thats perfect for a day out with family or friends. It has over 30 rides including roller coasters, a zipline, rope courses, and even a rain dance area. Theres also a kids zone, boating, and selfie spots all around. The vibe is energetic, and the place is quite spacious with food stalls and seating areas. Its open from 11 AM to 7 PM, and ticket prices are reasonable with separate options for rides and adventure activities. Great spot if youre in the mood for some thrill and chill in one place."),
("Hop up Jaipur","Jaipur","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://content3.jdmagicbox.com/v2/comp/jaipur/p1/0141px141.x141.231108175106.p6p1/catalogue/hopup-jawahar-circle-jaipur-gaming-zones-8PlEByFxtE.jpg","https://hopupindia.com/jaipur/ .","HopUp Jaipur is a lively indoor entertainment zone near Jawahar Circle, perfect for a fun day out with friends or family. Its got everything from go karting and trampolines to bowling, VR games, and arcade fun—all under one roof. The vibe is energetic, and the place is super modern with clean facilities and a café to chill at. Youll need a prepaid card to play, and while it can get a bit pricey, theres a lot packed in to make it worth it. Great spot if youre looking to mix thrills and games with a cool hangout vibe indoors."),
("New Hawai Jahaj","Jaipur","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSjUdP1gjmT7uXl4xO-nEJenZVYzMfC6M18YQ&s","https://www.newhawaijahaj.in/ ","New Hawai Jahaj in Jaipur is a popular and quirky family restaurant, especially known for its airplane themed setup. The whole place is styled like youre dining inside an aircraft, complete with airplane seats and staff dressed like cabin crew, which makes it a fun experience for kids and families. The menu is mostly Indian and Chinese, with decent variety and budget friendly prices. Its not a fancy fine dine spot, but more of a casual, theme based restaurant thats all about the experience rather than just the food. Good for something different and playful."),
("PUNO","Jaipur","Amusement/Theme Parks","https://media1.thrillophilia.com/filestore/ox0zau8gmt6zu0g2fyzamfi2roxz_DSC_0003.JPG","https://funatpuno.com/ .","Puno is an exciting, well run indoor adventure park offering dynamic trampoline fun, rope challenges, and kids friendly zones ideal for medium duration thrills with groups or families ."),
("Bapu Bazar","Jaipur","Markets","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSNZ7j1tWoMPkTTqoBUOUJM3uHXCny4GDqFgQ&s","https://jaipurtourism.co.in/bapu-bazar-jaipur .","Bapu Bazar in Jaipur is a lively market thats great for picking up traditional Rajasthani stuff like mojaris, handicrafts, block-printed clothes, and home décor. Its also a nice spot for trying local street food like kachoris, lassi, and falooda while youre browsing. The vibe is colorful and energetic, especially in the evenings. Bargaining is common, so dont shy away from negotiating a bit. Its one of those places where shopping and culture come together definitely worth a visit if youre in the city."),
("Jaipur Night Market","Jaipur","Markets","https://newstrack.com/h-upload/2023/03/02/1536026-night.webp","http://justdial.com/Jaipur/Jaipur-Night-Market-Opposite-Rajasthan-Haat-Johri-Bazar/0141PX141-X141-230312140549-X4S6_BZDET ",": Jaipur Night Market is a weekend highlight great vibes, cultural performances, tasty food, and a chance to shop under the stars. Reserve a 2hour evening slot and enjoy a lively, colorful night in the Pink City."),
("Dadich Market","Jaipur","Markets","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRXJYU-okB4QCV4yyUawRGTpoxgUlgjRqYfqA&s","https://www.justdial.com/Jaipur/Dadich-Market-Chandpole-Bazar/0141PX141-X141-220126002511-N7Q7_BZDET .","Dadich Market in Jaipur is a bustling local market mostly known for affordable clothing, kitchen items, and daily essentials. Its the kind of place where locals shop regularly, so prices are pretty reasonable. Youll find everything from fabrics and bags to home goods and even fresh fruits and veggies. The vibe is lively, a bit chaotic, but very authentic. It can get crowded, especially during the day, so going early is a good idea. If youre looking to explore local markets beyond the touristy ones, this one gives a more real slice of Jaipur life."),
("Jaipur Centre of Culture and Arts","Jaipur","Art and Culture","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT1NHnBEDMJ3zpXSOxDN-9ztP2YxYvCovohiA&s","https://www.jccaindia.com/ .","Jaipur Centre of Art and Culture is a nice spot if youre into traditional and contemporary art. It showcases a mix of Rajasthani heritage and modern creativity, with paintings, sculptures, crafts, and cultural events. Its a peaceful place to explore local talent and get a feel of Jaipurs artistic side."),
("Jawahar kala Kendra","Jaipur","Art and Culture","https://jaipurtourism.co.in/images/places-to-visit/header/jawahar-kala-kendra-jaipur-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg","https://jkk.artandculture.rajasthan.gov.in/content/ArtandCulture/en/jawahar-kala-kendra.html ","Jawahar Kala Kendra is a great place to dive into Jaipurs cultural scene. The architecture itself is pretty unique, and inside youll find art galleries, theatres, a library, and even a nice little coffee spot. They often host exhibitions, plays, and workshops, so theres always something creative happening. Its a peaceful yet vibrant space to explore art, culture, and local crafts."),
("The Art Ghar","Jaipur","Art and Culture","https://gos3.ibcdn.com/9ef7371d-ad2f-446e-96a3-80f807c5fb85.jpg","https://www.makemytrip.com/hotels/the_art_ghar-details-jaipur.html ","The Art Ghar in Jaipur is such a vibe part studio, part café, part boutique stay, and full time creativity hub. Think minimal, sun lit interiors with pink bougainvilleas, comfortable corners for sketching/reading, a curated store, and a menu that mixes wellness with seasonal comfort food ."),
("Albert hall Museum","Jaipur","Art and Culture","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQQ-QnpGEpa0oN7nS9YO0rY2u1YGeXcGwB4Vw&s","https://obms-tourist.rajasthan.gov.in/place-details/Government-Central-Museum-Albert-Hall-Jaipur .","Albert Hall Museum is definitely worth a stop in Jaipur especially if you love gorgeous architecture and fascinating artifacts. Picture strolling into a palace-like building with domes and murals, then exploring rooms filled with everything from antique instruments to Persian carpets and even an Egyptian mummy. The night-time lights give it a magical vibe too. Its easy to reach, not too expensive, and gives you a real taste of Rajasthans art, history, and royal flair. Totally recommend carving out 1 to 2 hours there—especially during the winter or evening visit!" ),
("Stepout Cafe","Jaipur","Cafes","https://d4t7t8y8xqo0t.cloudfront.net/resized/750X436/restaurant%2F662519%2Frestaurant120190322102820.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/stepout-cafe-c-scheme .","Stepout Café is such a gem bright, artsy interiors, a cozy book and coffee lounge, plus a great mix of healthy and indulgent food. Whether you want vegan pancakes or a killer brownie shake, theyve got you covered. Its open from 7:30 AM to around 10:30 PM, so you can swing by anytime morning coffee, midday hangout, or an evening chill out spot. Plus, its super comfy if you need to work or read there. Definitely a mustvisit in CScheme!" ),
("Cafe Quaint","Jaipur","Cafes","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/12/32/96/49/img-20180228-205116-largejpg.jpg?w=900&h=500&s=1","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/cafe-quaint-bapu-nagar ","Cafe Quaint at JKK is such a lovely find—vibrant, cozy, and laidback with that artsy charm youd expect inside the Kala Kendra. The menus always switch up with healthy bowls, waffles, Turkish eggs, and killer coldbrew. I love how you can just grab a book, play a board game, and stay for hours. Its open till around 9–10 PM, costs ₹600–₹1,200 for two, and they often have sweet offers. Totally a peaceful hangout!" ),
("Nibs Cafe and Chocolataria","Jaipur","Cafes","https://dineout-media-assets.swiggy.com/swiggy/image/upload/fl_lossy,f_auto,q_auto/v1661204594/aqyiudskujb0jfdple89.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/nibs-cafe-and-chocolataria-gopalbari ","Nibs Café & Chocolataria is such a cozy gem in CScheme—super colourful, with funky décor like scooter art and birdcage seats. Great for a lazy brunch or dessert mission: think rainbow lattes, Nutella waffles, rainbow shakes, pizza, pasta its a whole vibe. Open till 11 PM, about ₹800 to ₹950 for two, and the staff is really sweet. Perfect spot to chill with friends or treat yourself."),
("Curious Life Coffee Roasters","Jaipur","Cafes","https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/0/102620/0bc29fa23f97d4ae6d6a46df1f64ff72.jpg","https://www.zomato.com/jaipur/curious-life-coffee-roasters-c-scheme ","Curious Life in C Scheme is such a gem one of Jaipurs first specialty roastery cafés! The vibes calm yet buzzing, perfect for a solo coffee moment or a laid-back chat. They roast beans in house and serve everything from AeroPress to cold brew, along with tasty bites like muffins, paninis, and Buddha bowls. Around ₹650 to ₹800 for two, with no WiFi (so actually sweet, no distractions!),. If youre into good coffee, want a quiet spot to work, or feel like trying some single origin brews, its a top pick. Heads up: it can get a tad crowded during peak hours, but that just means folks love it too!"),
("Inox Crystal Palm","Jaipur","Movie Theatres","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSi_Hz5WGM_K8PBY2m7M2P8tJ6Auq5XQkDhzQ&s","n.bookmyshow.com/cinemas/jaip/inox-crystal-palm-c-scheme/INJC/2025061 ","INOX at Crystal Palm is a really nice spot if youre planning a chill movie day its comfy, clean, and has great visuals with Dolby Atmos. Tickets are budgetfriendly (₹180 to 300),, and the snack bar is decent enough (just maybe skip buying water inside ),. Its right inside the mall too, so you can shop, eat, and watch all in one place. Heads Up: the airconditioning can be hit or miss and showtimes might start a bit late sometimes, but overall its feel good cinema for a weekend or weekday unwind. Fancy watching something this weekend?" ),
("Raj Mandir Cinema","Jaipur","Movie Theatres","https://ebnw.net/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/102443a55f0ad5d559dd205b9f0b08e6.jpg","https://in.bookmyshow.com/cinemas/jaip/rajmandir-cinema-dolby-atmos-jaipur/RMCJ/20250619 .","Raj Mandir is the place to see a Bollywood movie in Jaipur it feels like a royal night out. The buildings classic Art Deco look, giant velvet curtains, grand chandeliers and Dolby Atmos sound make it an experience. Grab tickets early for the balcony if you can, and expect lots of cheers and claps from the audience. Its part of the fun! Tickets are super affordable (~₹100 to 350),, and even if youre just there for the vibe, its worth it. Want tips on showtimes or how to grab decent seats?" ),
("Golcha Cinema","Jaipur","Movie Theatres","https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0d/49/bd/c8/golcha-cinema.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1","https://in.bookmyshow.com/cinemas/jaip/golcha-cinema-jaipur/GOLC/20250619 ","Golcha Cinema is one of those classic Jaipur gems—pink, Art Deco style, and dating all the way back to 1954. Its got that nostalgic charm with old school ticket counters and samosa stalls, plus humble ticket prices. It now has 3 screens and even hosts film festivals. Just a heads up: its not a high tech multiplex, so sound is decent but picture quality might wobble, and some people mention worn seats and not so great washrooms. But hey, if you want a slice of Jaipurs cinematic heritage on a budget this is it! Fancy checking out a show and grabbing a samosa?"),
("Cinepolis Triton","Jaipur","Movie Theatres","https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRwb_2TtPuzCWsptLSp2sPCmQp6HA3l7fywLQ&s","https://in.bookmyshow.com/cinemas/jaip/cinepolis-triton-mega-mall-jaipur/FNJJ/20250619 ","Cinepolis at Triton Mall is a really chill option for a movie day in Jaipur. Theyve got comfy recliners, top notch Dolby Atmos audio, and easy ticketing (phone apps FTW!),. Since its inside a big mall with parking, food court, and even a gaming zone, its a super convenient shop, grab a bite, and then catch a flick. Tickets are wallet friendly too (₹180 to 350),. Heads up: lifts in the mall can be slow but inside the theatre its clean, comfy and hassle free. Fancy catching a show here this weekend?"),
("Step Well","Jaipur","Hidden Gems","https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-674x446/06/6e/b5/4b.jpg","https://www.artisansofleisure.com/luxury-travel-blog/2023/01/visiting-an-ancient-stepwell-in-jaipur-rajasthan-in-india/ ","Panna Meena Ka Kund is such a hidden gem near Amer Fort! Its this super cool step well with diamond patterned stairs that criss cross eight levels down into deep, green water. The bottom is pleasantly cooler—great escape from Jaipurs heat and the symmetry is just jaw dropping. Totally free, open sunrise to sunset, and an epic spot for photos. Its pretty chill too, no crowds like the big tourist sites. If youre up for architecture, history, or just a neat experience, youve gotta check it out. Want directions or the best time to go?"),
("Monkey Temple ","Jaipur","Hidden Gems","https://www.ghumindiaghum.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Jaipur-Monkey-Temple-%E2%80%93-Galtaji-Jaipur.jpg","https://www.laurewanders.com/monkey-temple-jaipur/ ","Monkey Temple (aka Galta Ji), is such a peaceful little escape tucked in the hills outside Jaipur. Its got these serene old temples and natural water tanks that locals believe are holy. But yeah the main stars are the monkeys! Youll find loads of them just chilling around. Its a bit of a climb to reach, but totally worth it for the views and that quiet vibe. Best to go early morning or late afternoon when its cooler. Want directions or tips on what to carry?"),
("Flower Market","Jaipur","Hidden Gems","https://www.wildfrontierstravel.com/media/cache/page_image_large/upload/mirror/www-wildfrontierstravel-com/c17f74b8_Flower%20Market%201.jpeg","https://www.anikapannu.com/post/the-jaipur-wholesale-flower-market ","Jaipurs flower market is honestly one of those local gems you have to catch at dawn. Its full of color and that fresh flower smell hits you right away marigolds, jasmine, roses, all getting bundled into garlands or baskets. Its super local, lively, and a great peek into daily life. Just go early, like before 8 AM, and wear comfy shoes youll be walking through narrow lanes full of vendors, scooters, and scent trails. Want help locating the closest one or best time to go?"),
("World Trade Park","Jaipur","Shopping malls","https://jaipurbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/world-trade-park_9.jpg?w=840","https://www.baume-et-mercier.com/en/stores/details.002485.world-trade-park-mall-jaipur.html ","World Trade Park is Jaipurs goto mega mall its gorgeous inside, with themed streets, a massive food court, chic cafés, luxury and midrange brands, and a top-notch Cinepolis VIP. Plus it has a gaming zone, kids play area, and even plans for an underwater restaurant! Easy to reach, open late, and always buzzing with a solid crowd. Perfect for a full day hangout shop, eat, play, and catch a film. Want info on current events there or best times to visit? "),
("Crystal Court Mall","Jaipur","Shopping  malls","https://d3gw4aml0lneeh.cloudfront.net/assets/locations/14993/FzNUk52dwdqO.jpg","https://www.justdial.com/Jaipur/Crystal-Court-Mall-Near-G-T-Malviya-Nagar/0141P1425-1425-110316140628-T4E9_BZDET ","Crystal Court Mall is a solid choice in Malviya Nagar—packed with brands like Levis, Spykar, Cantabil, and even a Vishal Mega Mart for budget finds. Youve got food options from fast food to a rooftop bar, plus salons, a gaming zone, a cinema you name it. Its open daily 11 AM to 10 PM, super studentfriendly and buzzing. Parkings in the basement but can fill up on busy days, and bargaining is a thing at the smaller stalls. Overall, a fun onestop spot for a hangout with friends or family. Want help finding the best parking times or the nearest metro stop?"),
("Mall of Jaipur","Jaipur","Shopping Malls","https://www.fsrealty.co.in/images/800/website-image/Mall-Of-Jaipur.jpg","https://www.fsrealty.co.in/mall-of-jaipur.html ","Mall of Jaipur in Vaishali Nagar is a pretty slick spot bright, roomy, with trendy shops like Shoppers Stop, plus a cute bazaar zone downstairs for bargain finds. The big draw? A PVR multiplex with Luxe seats and even 4DX if youre feeling fancy. Its chill, not too crowded, and easy to park. Just a heads-up: food options are mostly cinema snacks and Costa has no proper food court yet. Perfect if youre in the mood for a relaxed shopping cum movie day. Want to check showtimes or know the quieter hours?" );



